<br>
ooc well, I have a few moments while I mooch one of my friends internet connections.<br>
<br>
First, thanks.  These are the kinds of things that make me all giddy feeling... when people tell me they are impressed with how I play Donnalinna.  It makes all the work worth it.<br>
<br>
Anyway, just a few more things to think about.<br>
<br>
1) ooc as Kaishia said, when Donnalinna was around, I upset her more than I thought I did.  So... if you do RP, please let people know you are, and make sure they're not really mad or upset with you.  I am sorry Kaishia, and I'm glad you took me aside to remind me of this.  And, to anyone else who I have upset unknowingly, I am sorry as well.  I didn't mean to upset you; I was simply trying to stay in character so you all can further immerse  youself in the EQ universe.<br>
<br>
To Kaishia<br>
<br>
ooc well... honestly, what's wrong with a girl being girly?  I'm not saying you're not right being tomboyish (it makes you happy, and it's who you are), but if a girl enjoys doing feminine stuff, that should be okay too.  So... I chose to have Donnalinna be feminine and girly.  She could have just as easily been quiet and reserved, shy, spunky and outgoing, etc., etc., etc.  I just choose girly, as... well without runing Donnalinna's secret for everyone else... it fit best with her past, and what her upbringing would have been.<br>
<br>
To Ally,<br>
<br>
Something else to remember too.  Story-wise, if a girl talks about herself in the third person, she's suppossed to be pure of heart and innocent... or attempting to keep her innocence.  (For example, little girls sometimes talk about themselves in the third person in real-life, its kinda funny-cute sort of thing.)  So... Donnalinna might talk about herself in the third person because she is nobility... and it also might be for another reason too.<br>
<br>
To Legolass<br>
<br>
Oh, you're just jellous that Donnalinna has more of a following than you do ;P  Besides... if you slap her, she might get really indignant with you, and slap you back.<br>
<br>
Donnalinna's Avatar<br>
